Fantaip is a "Phantom IP" program that listens on a secondary IP address that we will use to receive response information to without confusing the kernel. To use fantaip, type 'fantaip (interface) (ip)', Ex., 'fantaip eth0 192.168.140.53'. 



Usage: fantaip (options) IP
	-d		Detach from terminal and daemonize
	-H		Hardware address like XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX (otherwise use nics hwaddr)
	-h		help
	-i		*interface
	-v		verbose operation
*: Argument required
Example: fantaip -i eth0 192.168.1.7
